body:
#### Issue details

When i create a Table after that i call row() and then i add an item is expected that that this item is in the next line. 

In Libgdx version 1.6.5 i create a TextButton with some text then i called row() to add a new label to this button. This label will be in a new line but after libgdx version 1.7.0 this label will be in the right side of the previous label. 

This image was taken using 1.6.5.
![screen shot 2016-07-08 at 9 23 58 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3458265/16688803/65eb05a2-4552-11e6-817e-88551bcb01b1.png)

And this one using the latest release 1.9.3.
![screen shot 2016-07-08 at 9 26 00 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3458265/16688849/a0b49ba8-4552-11e6-8c96-84d17979ba50.png)
#### Reproduction steps/code

I created a simple code. Using the default skin. 

``` java
public class TableBug extends ApplicationAdapter {

    public Skin skin;
    Stage stage;
    Table container;


    @Override
    public void create() {
        skin = new Skin(Gdx.files.internal("UI/uiskin.json"));

        container = new Table();
        container.setFillParent(true);


        stage = new Stage();
        stage.addActor(container);

    }

    @Override
    public void render() {
        Gdx.gl.glClearColor(1, 0, 0, 1);
        Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);

        stage.act();
        stage.draw();

        if (Gdx.input.justTouched()) {
            TextButton newButton = new TextButton("Button ", skin);
            container.row();
            container.add(newButton);
        }
    }
}
```
#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies

version 1.7.0 and up
#### Please select the affected platforms
- [ yes] Android
- [ yes] iOS (robovm)
- [ yes] iOS (MOE)
- [ yes] HTML/GWT
- [ yes] Windows
